intrepid souls who don't have a lot jump into the business anyway.
And many of them do well. Which brings us _ and them _ to the Napa
Wine Company here on Route 29. In the wine trade, the company is
known as a custom crush facility, meaning it makes wine in someone
else's winery. By Frank J. Prial.
