<HEADER>
A7836 &Cx1f; tad-z
u l BC-DADS-BATHROOM-COX     08-24 0629
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-DADS-BATHROOM-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COMMENTARY: Daughters' dads and bathroom stall tatics.
 &HT;    By Todd C. Duncan
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ So, am I the only the only single father in America
who has to deal with this?
</P>
<P>
   I make sure my 6-year-old daughter goes before we leave the
house. We arrive at the theater, load up on popcorn, soda and
little candy bears. We find the two best seats in the house and
await the next Jim Henson spectacular.
</P>
<P>
   Then, just when Miss Piggy is about to eat up a scene: ``Daddy,
I have to go!''
</P>
<P>
   We scramble out of the dark theater and race to the bathrooms.
</P>
<P>
   The line to use the ladies' room snakes around the corner, but
that's not our destination. We rush into the men's room, find a
stall and ensure cleanliness, and then I leave her alone to
complete the mission.
</P>
<P>
   Recently, such trips have drawn the ire and shock of some of the
men's room customers. Not the little boys, however _ they're too
busy concentrating on target management. It's adult men who are
freaking out.
</P>
<P>
   One man in his 40s said, ``Hey, this is a men's room.''
</P>
<P>
   Speaking low enough so my daughter can't hear my selection of
juicy words, I proceed to tell the man of my fatherly
responsibility and question his desire to condemn my actions. After
a few minutes, he apologizes and admits he was wrong to question my
parental acumen.
</P>
<P>
   What did he think was going to happen?
</P>
<P>
   The fact that a man would even think of something ``going
wrong,'' as one man said to me, is so perverse. What does he mean
by ``going wrong?''
</P>
<P>
   My daughter is a small child. She is blind to any sexual
overtones and there shouldn't be any in the bathroom anyway. The
little boys she quickly passes on the way to an unused stall are
not at all disturbed by her presence.
</P>
<P>
   Why are some men, and maybe some women, so put off by such a
simple action?
</P>
<P>
   We as a community don't even look twice when a mother takes her
6-year-old son into the ladies' room. Now, it's true that women
complete their missions behind closed doors, but why are they given
the benefit of the doubt as caretakers and dads aren't? My
intentions to care for my child are no different.
</P>
<P>
   When I was growing up, it was true that friendly men and women
would help single parents by offering to usher the boys or girls to
their respective bathrooms.
</P>
<P>
   The sad reality is that in today's climate, when horrible acts
of cruelty are committed against children every day, I cannot risk
a stranger taking my child anywhere.
</P>
<P>
   I once let a young woman take my daughter into the restroom of a
store. I waited just outside the door, listening for the slightest
sound of distress or trouble. It was the longest and most
nerve-racking four minutes of my life. Nothing happened, but if
something had occurred, I would have never forgiven myself.
</P>
<P>
   Should my need to protect my daughter subject me to suspicion
and condemnation? I think not.
</P>
<P>
   I know that my daughter soon will start seeking and be granted
total bathroom independence.
</P>
<P>
   We have discussed what to do if a stranger says or does
something she feels is not right almost as many times as I've read
Winnie the Pooh adventures to her at bedtime.
</P>
<P>
   She'll fly solo very soon, and I won't have to deal with
uptight, nosy male jerks. But why did I ever have to?
</P>
<P>
   It's funny, we see commercials and newspapers ads every day in
this country that slam men for not taking an active role in their
children's lives. Do whatever it takes to protect and nurture your
child, the messages bellow.
</P>
<P>
   Isn't that what dads like me have been doing?
</P>
<P>
   Todd C. Duncan is an editor for Cox News Service in Atlanta.
E-mail tduncan(at)coxnews.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
