<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   EUROPE-GREENS (Brussels) _ Fifteen years after Europe's radical
green parties first became a significant political force, they have
their hands on the levers of power in five countries and are
knocking on the door in seven others. To gain and hold power they
are making compromises on issues, moves they earlier would have
branded as sellouts. By Kevin Cullen. 1570 words.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-PUTIN (Moscow) _ With his angular face, thinning hair and
pursed lips, Vladimir Putin looks like a high school vice
principal. In fact, he was a spy chief who learned to control
officials by blackmailing them with dirt. It looks like he'll use
that method to torpedo Boris Yeltsin's political opponents, too. By
Brian Whitmore. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
