<P>
   INDIANOLA, Texas _ Indianola, on Matagorda Bay, has been
forgotten in Texas history. Even now, with the dying fury of
Hurricane Bret holding the public's attention, this tiny town is
never mentioned. It is not known. Yet, more than 100 years ago,
Indianola was considered the second-largest seaport in Texas.
Second to Galveston. Hurricanes blew it off the map, destroyed it
twice and returned it to native sand and rock. They all but erased
its place in the development of the state. By ART CHAPMAN. Story
has moved in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
