<P>
   UNDATED _ I know the difference between a hat trick and a field
goal. I know the difference between a nine-iron and a sand wedge _
even though I'm terrible with a sand wedge. This spring, I used one
to dig holes for my flower bed. I just put a practice ball on the
spot where I wanted to plant the bulb and pretended I was in a sand
trap. I never did hit that ball, but my petunias were gorgeous.
And, yes, I know the difference between a Mustang and a Corvette.
These are simple matters. But what is the difference between,
``Mom, you don't have to come,'' and ``Mom, you don't need to
come?'' By MONICA FRAZIER ANDERSON. Story has moved ``l'' lifestyle
category. &QL; 
