   SEMTECH-TURNAROUND (Los Angeles) _ Nearly a year after the Asian
crisis battered chip maker Semtech Corp., the Newbury Park firm is
on a rebound. The company is expected to announce strong quarterly
earnings on Tuesday. And the company's stock has already
experienced a stunning turnaround, rising from a low of around
$10.375 last year to $68 at the close of markets Monday. By Jason
Takenouchi.
