<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUSINESS </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   (Repeating budget for AMs and PMs of Aug. 25.)
</P>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Aug. 25 and thereafter. The stories will carry the ``f''
financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For questions
about stories, contact Susan Leh at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   LLOYD-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Let the hire beware. Daily News
columnist Ken Lloyd, Ph.D., a specialist in organizational
behavior, answers readers' questions on workplace ethics and
relationships.
</P>
<P>
   GAS-PRICES (Los Angeles) _ Labor Day holiday travelers are
expected to take to the road in near record numbers, but they will
be paying more to fuel their journeys, according to a report. By
Gregory Wilcox.
</P>
<P>
   EXTENSION-CORDS (Los Angeles) _ Michael Nostrant started one of
those businesses that would make most people say, ``Why didn't I
think of that?'' The founder of SNS International in Tarzana sells
Jelly Cords, extension cords that come in 14 colors. By Deborah
Adamson.
</P>
