<P>
   Lead story:
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-SECT (Shanghai, China) _ Chinese authorities announce they
are preparing to prosecute senior members of Falun Gong, the
spiritual movement that was banned last month after it startled
China's leaders with its ability to organize potent anti-government
protests. To deliver a strong message that Beijing will tolerate no
protests of any kind, the authorities are now expected to charge
Falun Gong's leaders with subversion and direct that they be
sentenced to life in prison. By Seth Faison. (The story has moved
in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   Top center story:
</P>
<P>
   FED-RATES (Washington) _ The Federal Reserve votes for the
second time in less than two months to raise interest rates by a
quarter of a percentage point, saying the action should help avert
inflation while allowing the long economic expansion to continue.
By Richard W. Stevenson. (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET in
``f'' news file.) 1,100 words.
</P>
<P>
   With photo and graphic.
</P>
<P>
   2-column photo reefer to TURKEY-QUAKE; story inside.
</P>
