</P>
<P>
   BERGER-PROFILE (Washington) _ Widely regarded as the president's
closest foreign policy aide, perhaps the most influential national
security adviser since Henry Kissinger, Sandy Berger is at bottom a
political rather than strategic figure. Unlike the professors,
diplomats and military officers who have for the most part preceded
