   (NYT24) MT. KISCO, N.Y. -- Aug. 24, 1999 -- FED-RATES, 08-24 --
Construction of a housing development in Mt. Kisco. The Federal
Reserve voted Tuesday to raise interest rates by a quarter of a
percentage point for the second time in less than two months. The
changes are intended to slow the economy by putting upward pressure
on the borrowing rates, or at least to help lock in a general rise
over much of this year in the rates set by the financial markets,
from mortgages to corporate bond offerings. (Janet Durrans/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT23) MINNEAPOLIS -- Aug. 24, 1999 -- MINNEAPOLIS-AIRLINE,
08-24 -- A jet with Sun Country Airlines, a small carrier that
started flying a regular schedule to 15 destinations in June, taxis
near airliners with Northwest, the nations fourth largest carrier.
Most cities root unabashedly for a home-town business to make it
big. But here, where Northwest Airlines has its headquarters,
employs 21,000, and controls 80 percent of the airline seats out of
the city, many people are rooting for Sun Country Airlines. (Steve
Woit/New York Times Photo)
</P>
