drizzled with fruity olive oil; it is charred, peeled and blended
into a silky, garlicky puree; it is layered with tomatoes, onions
and oil, and baked until it is creamy and caramelized. Eggplants
are even cooked in sugar syrup and eaten as a sweet. (Tony
Cenicola/New York Times Photo)
