<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUSINESS-TRAVEL-NYT </SLUG>
  
 BUSINESS TRAVEL: CROWDED PLANES; AIRLINE UPDATE; WILL CARNIVAL BUY
PRINCESS?  (Duplication warning: also moving in `t' category) 
(mk) 
 By EDWIN McDOWELL   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   If you wonder whether the flights you have been on in recent
months are always crowded, or whether you are just a victim of bad
timing or bad luck, the load factors _ the percentages of available
seats occupied by paying passengers _ for most U.S. airlines last
month are revealing. So are the year-to-date load factors.
</P>
